hmm its been so weird.  lately right after tennis i become exhausted.  not tired, EXHAUSTED.  No matter what my diet is or the amount of sleep I get, this cycle has been going on all week.  My body temperature hasnt shifted between about 95.6-97 for the past few days.  I researched it online and maybe i should go see a doctor.  it might be a thyroid problem apparently because ive suffered bad depressions, major pre menstrual problems, and weight gain, memory problems, and abnormally slow thinking as well. hmmmm...ill see how my body temperature fairs today.

nates bday party was fun.  i got a little pissed at darin.  he's not my favorite person and then he made a jerk comment so i was ready to leave.  garden state was such an awesome movie and scrabble was fun except for that last pick of 7 vowels that cost me the game wah.

my friends are all taking the new SATs.  goood luck!  i take em in may, and tonight is junior miss.

i'm feeling super nostalgic, but it's been worse. Have you ever had that feeling-that crappy one...the one where you know you're never going to see someone again? All last year I lived in my little naive moment every moment. When they started crying saying we were never going to see eachother again, i hadn't understood. Now I do. It makes me sick to think of everyone and how we're all living our seperate lives when once we were so close. how i haven't even sent or received any letters or postcards and have only called u cait. So sick...things wont' ever be the same, even if i go back. When I look at my pictures lately i have to take a deep breath and tell myself that it was real...i really did walk along that street over a bazillion times. i once only spoke french and didnt even have to worry the SATs or grades or school pretty much in general. The Alps were real, the clubs were real, the people were real, the pain was real, the joy was real, the excitement was real, the eiffel tower really does exist, the moulin rouge really does exist. I know I'll romanticize things too much...I already am. I know things will never be the same when I go back. I haven't even really kept in contact with my host families...god im so lazy and so poor to even afford to send a present. god i actually have no excuse. I AM THE UNOFFICIAL CANARICAN! I miss you lamborels...

woke up late- was lazy. saw dee daniels and attended her workshop which was awesome.  tried to watch "lady be good" but musicians don't really interest me, even if they are women...i was hoping for some vocalists.
saw andrew play bass and it was pretty awesome...especially when you went crazy on that second song and we all clapped.
lazied around.  tried to make mom a birthday cake but it ended up less than an inch high and green.  she was in a nobody likes me everybody hates me mood anywho.

Hm I think I used to feel ashamed for not being as appreciative of certain bands and music as some of my friends, but honestly, I can listen to Hendrix and like him, but don't sue me if I'm not bowing down to him and worshipping him at your depth.  I really tend to focus more on and vocalists and lyricists.

This festival has revamped my singing passion, horrah!  

If anyone knows of any other competition or performance opportunities let me know.

Grab your coat and get your hat leave your worry on the doorstep just direct your feet to the sunny side of the street Can't you hear a pitter-pat? and that happy tune is your step life can be so sweet on the sunny side of the street i used to walk in the shade with those blues on parade but i'm not afraid this rover, crossed over if i never had a cent I'd be rich as Rockefeller! Gold dust at my feet on the sunny side of the street.

It felt good.  It felt good, so I'm ecstatic.  All I wanted was to feel comfortable, have fun, and be happy with my performance, and all of the above were acheived.

I went to first period choir then took katrin and went to this dance workshop which ended up for people who have never taken dance so we left because it was boring, however, I know the teacher phyllis gooden-young?  having taken dance classes with before, and i like her.
we went back to my place and i took a shower and got ready with my hot outfit, black pumps, sparkly make-up and a flower in my hair and i warmed up for her and ian.
we went to the hartung where i warmed up and was up first from moscow.  i felt really good about my performance and i got some nice compliments.

sorry i was going to make this brief...but here

so, i didn't win nor did jessica and the two girls who did...were incredible.  Like, you hear our choir and you think aw how nice they're in tune and that sweet soloist. but these chicks were up with diana krall.  in fact, in all honesty i would have chosen the second singer's cd over diana krall's.  yes, they were effing indescribable.  I was smiling and had tingles listening to the performances at the concert tonight.

GEORGE CARSON WON and he did an amazing performance-the audience loved him. CONGRADULATIONS!

God, I love jazz and I'm so thankful for this festival and how it gets me motivated to spend more time creating music and appreciating the art of such an emotional, expressive, and laid-back style.  hallelujah.

Tomorrow I'll hopefully be attending performances by something-or-another feather, dee daniels (seriously amazing singer), and im gonna watch that documentary lady be good.  thats my plan at least.  oh and ya, krystyn, i saw Jane Monheit- she did some kick-arse scat.

Title : Little Acorns
Artist : The White Stripes
Album : Elephant


When problems overwhelm us and sadness smothers us where do we find the will and the courage to continue? Well the answer may come in the caring voice of a friend,a chance encounter with a book, or from a personal faith.
For Janet help came from her faith, but it also from a squirrel. Shortly after her divorce, Janet lost her father, then she lost her job.
She had mounting money problems. But Janet not only survived she worked her way out of despondency and now she says, life is good again. How could this happen? She told me that late one ??? day when she was at her lowest she watched a squirrel storing up nuts for the winter, one at a time he would take them to the nest. And she thought, if that squirrel
can take care of himself with the harsh winter coming along, then so can I. Once I ripped my problems into small pieces I was able to carry them,just like those acorns, one at a time.

Take all your problems
And rip 'em apart
Oh Oh Oh
Carry them off
In a shopping cart
Oh Oh Oh

And another thing you
Should've known from the start
The problems in hand
Are lighter than at heart

Be like the squirrel, girl
Be like the squirrel
Give it a whirl, girl
Be like the squirrel

And another thing
You have to know in this world
Cut up your hair
Straighten your curls
Well you problems
Hide in your curls

Well, I'm performing tomorrow at 1pm, and I'm not nervous...actually I'm a bit nervous of getting nervous because, more than anything, I really want to get up there, have fun, and give an outstanding performance-I don't care about placement.  (yesterday my mom and i with help of adiddy got THE cutest jazz outfit for me!  hoorah!) Right after me Friday is Jessica, then Lara, then Pauline from MHS.
I think I might take some dance workshops in the morning like the great dances of broadway cuz i really really miss lorraine's jazz technique.  i hope it's not for beginners and not super easy though :(.

It happened.  I took on way too much and i just got so stressed yesterday...unfortunately in front of Ian, but he gave me some very well placed advice and everything is magically better somehow.  awesome friend. im gonna drop ballet and now im doing tennis and jazz dance and voice lessons and thats the extra curricular crap now.  i realized that in order not to be a complete day-dreaming dolt at school i have to get to sleep earlier, and...

read my next post for some nice advice from the white stripes...

super sorry about that last entry...man!  I need to get out though I think...i need a change of atmosphere-my sister says i need an adventure and im apt to agree with her.  i need to go rock climbing or on a hike with fellow adventurer ian.  i need to get away for the summer and really go work at an art museum and live with one of my aunts.  i need to dump whatever's giving me this cynical and pessismistic outlook.
hmm i want to go to mount holyoke or wellesley really bad...but i also want to be in an urban area really bad.
i miss the city. i miss the noise, the hustle, the life, the diversity, the culture of the city.

and-one big embrace for you all for making life better sometimes and teaching me how to think differently.

hmm wow-bethany's comment helped me see something in a different light which was nice.  I wish our breakup could have been handled so much more maturely.  i tried talking to him many times- i truly wanted to maintain a friendship with him even though times were hard...but his responses lead me to really believe that he just didn't care.  i didnt want to believe he cared so little about me anyway but i wonder if someday he'll look back whenever that day is and go...hmmm maybe i could have handled that differently. 
last night we saw the mumbles and purl.  the guy in the mumbles reminded me completely o fjack white but smaller.  purl was really awesome but the singer should scream more...sing less and one of the guitarists looked so much like billy corgan- im super tempted to go to their concert this friday in pullman if i can.
theres a free concert at the SUB feb 16.  Bang Bang is the band or something?  i really wanna go.
katrin and i went bikini shopping yesterday too and saw kt and lexi for a breif while it was pretty funny.  we were dancing around in bikinis in the zumiez dressing room and all i could think was...if only zach were here now haha.  i like the frilly green one!
I hung out mostly with ian.  never even imagined a lot of this...it's really great.  i think we're on the same level in so many things.

mmm today = super :D. tonight = absolutely indescribable.
"c'etait incroyable"  warm fuzzies warm fuzzies.

I went with katie, katie, shinai, becca, and lexi to the pita pit today but let me tell you, Jared Lien walking straight into the pole made my day, man.  i fell i was laughing so hard and started crying...even the bus driver who saw him said "oooh, better get a liscence plate number for that sign".

"Boogeyman" was pretty scary.

take my hand-we're off to neva-neverland...

haha katrin made me laugh so hard i almost peed my pants tonight.  we have to do this cheesy hop step for one of our dances and we were being videotaped so suddenly she goes off on this native american dance and im like wtf hahahaha it was excellent- i joined in.
then after we finished she looks at me out of nowhere and was like i LOVe doing this when im drunk- and started doing the robot.  
apparently her and i have the most "expression" in our lyrical dance- we did a happy dance when our teacher told us so and jessie was like psh rub it in haha.

okay this is a gross story but of course fascinating: umm so katie and jessie and amanda were telling us about how one time at a ballet class last semester this guy stood outside the door just watching them NAKED and im not sure how he got away from the director but he did and when they went out there to "go to the bathroom" there was a puddle of "man".
A;OWIEJHGAIOWJGE3;AIOWJ3G;I!!!!!!!!!!EWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWW AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH

on a different disgusting note:
My dad told me before i left he never had a child like me who was so disrespectful, terrible blah blah then told me to get out and didnt want to talk to me.  i asked him how i could change for better but he just shook his head at me.  i thought jessie said he was on my side?  for once id love to share how I felt-not in an angsty teenage way but really just say that I feel lonely, I want to be able to talk to them and that I don't walk out on purpose when they're talking but sometimes I'm afraid they'll say something mean to me.

I got my grade report- i have a 3.7 gpa and my parents didnt even look...not even after i told them it was there.  i wanted to go to swing dancing tonight but cant because apparently my mom "never sees me study for school".

hmmdy doo.  i pretty much just take it-i mean theyre my parents.  i really really though feel hopeless and it stresses me out sometimes...really bad.  I have no idea what to do-its frustrating and all i want to do is escape somehow...
that pms depression most likely wasnt pms.  i think i subconsiously take in the pain and stress cuz i cant really express it unless i decide to throw my chest of drawers across the room again.  so i guess i just get depressed and "dont know why" and my whole back is a rock *sigh*.  but i feel strangely optimistic and peaceful.

hung out with the ian and andrew after school fun stuff.

I'm really glad my mom bought this Madeline Peyroux cd.  She's like a modern Billie Holiday which is exquisite my friend.
My final paper for English was on a link I found between the books we read in class and a liberal anti-establishment theme.  I got a 43/50 and a B+ in the class- Mr. Hill was like, this is gonna be higher this semester, right?  I think I will just kick some ass this semester.
I thought having U.S. History with the sophmores would suck, but Mr. Wear seems like a nice guy and I sit behind Sara Young's beautiful hair.  I also sit near Emma who/m? everyone seems to know but me...Christian really wants me to switch to Hoogsteen with him which would kick, but I'm pretty apathetic.
It's kind of funny to analyze the people in the class-and judging ONLY from that class, I feel like there is a bit of a maturity gap just from one year.  It's interesting and I cannot believe that I was living alone in France at "their age".  What the hell was I thinking.  Oh but when I think that I love myself for having guts- I also know I'd do it again in a heartbeat.
I'm thinking about giving L'etranger by Albert Camus a chance again.  I read it last year and found it pretty bland yet melodramatic and I'm wondering if I'd appreciate it now.  Plus, I really really wanna read in French again- I'm jealous the seniors are reading Candide-that sounds like a kick arse book.
I wish I were uglier-is that wrong?  To tell you the truth I think that people respect ugly people more...that the compliments I'd recieve would have nothing to do with fleeting physical beauty.  I wouldn't be so disgustingly vain and distracted by my physical appearance, nor distract anyone else from more important things.
ryan parks is an awesome guy.  i enjoy talking with him because he is so open-minded, accepting and wise and he makes me feel bad when im immature haha.  (that whole martin thing).
and how could i let you go without saying
ian rocks.

well thursday finals ended and i went out to eat at teds (so greasy...soo gooood), i hung out with ian, what the hell did i do?! umm i hung out with shinai and katie then i went to dance and our class consisted of me, katrin and nicole which was pretty neat.  
our dance teacher likes me a lot which makes me feel good cuz she rocks too. then my dad came in to class 10 min before it ended and said that mom was made i took her car without asking (even though i did the day before and it was fine?) and so he had to take it back so i was like w/ever...went with katin to her house to get ready then went swing dancing.  
Swing dancing kicked my butt it was awesome and i loved lindy hop and being dipped!
